      "text": "Section 3\nPre-Trip Checklist & Travel Preparation\nThis section should be reviewed approximately:\n30 days before departure\n14 days before departure\n7 days before departure\n48 hours before departure\nThe goal is simple:\nEliminate surprises.\n30 Days Before Departure\nPassports\nVerify:\n□ Passport is packed in a safe location\n□ Passport expiration date is valid\n□ Passport photos saved to phones\n□ Emergency contact information updated\nFlights\nVerify:\n□ Delta reservation visible in Delta app\n□ EasyJet reservation visible in EasyJet app\n□ Seat assignments correct\n- \n- \n- \n- \n1\n\n□ Checked baggage included\nAccommodations\nVerify:\n□ Wedding Night reservation confirmed\n□ Paris Airbnb reservation confirmed\n□ Villa Gianlica reservation confirmed\n□ Moxy Pompeii reservation confirmed\nTickets Still Needed\nPurchase:\n□ Eiffel Tower Summit\n□ Louvre\n□ Versailles Passport\nThese are the only major missing reservations.\nTravel Apps\nInstall:\n□ Google Maps\n□ Uber\n□ Bolt\n□ WhatsApp\n□ Delta\n2\n\n□ EasyJet\n14 Days Before Departure\nFinancial Preparation\nVerify:\n□ Credit cards active\n□ Travel notices added if desired\n□ Backup card packed\n□ ATM card packed\nMobile Phones\nVerify:\n□ International plan active if desired\n□ Wi-Fi calling enabled\n□ Charging cables packed\n□ Portable charger packed\nPacking Supplies\nPurchase if needed:\n□ Sunscreen\n□ Waterproof phone pouch\n□ Luggage tags\n□ Portable battery pack\n3\n\n□ European outlet adapters\nClothing Check\nParis requires:\nComfortable walking shoes\nLight layers\nSmall umbrella\nAmalfi requires:\nSwimsuits\nSandals\nSunglasses\nSummer clothing\nPompeii requires:\nComfortable sneakers\n7 Days Before Departure\nPrint or Save\nSave screenshots of:\n□ Flight confirmations\n□ Airbnb confirmation\n□ Villa confirmation\n□ Moxy confirmation\n□ Cruise confirmation\n□ Capri confirmation\n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n4\n\nCreate Backup Folder\nOn both phones:\nCreate album named:\n\"Honeymoon Documents\"\nSave:\nFlights\nHotels\nTour confirmations\nPassport photos\nAirport Transportation\nVerify:\n□ Uber available for Carrollton departure\n□ Uber available for ATL return\nFinal Dining Reservations\nOptional:\nReserve:\n□ Le Volant\n□ Pink Mamma\n□ Bosco de' Medici\nNone are absolutely required.\n- \n- \n- \n- \n5\n\n72 Hours Before Departure\nWeather Check\nReview:\nParis forecast\nPraiano forecast\nCapri forecast\nPompeii forecast\nAdjust packing if necessary.\nTransportation Review\nRead:\nTransportation Appendix\nEspecially:\nParis taxi instructions\nPraiano buses\nNaples airport departure plan\n48 Hours Before Departure\nCritical Items\nThese are the most important items remaining.\nParis Airbnb\nObtain:\n- \n- \n- \n6\n\n□ Lockbox instructions\n□ Exact street number\n□ Entry directions\nTake screenshots immediately.\nCapri Tour\nVerify:\n□ Final boarding location\n□ Meeting time\n□ Marina instructions\nTake screenshots immediately.\nCooking Class\nConfirm:\n□ Actual start time\n□ Meeting location\nThe confirmation currently conflicts with planning notes.\nResolve before departure.\nNight Before Wedding Night\nPack separately:\nCarry-On Bag\nInclude:\n7\n\n□ Passport\n□ Wallet\n□ Credit cards\n□ Medications\n□ Phone charger\n□ Portable battery\n□ Headphones\n□ Light jacket\nNever check these items.\nChecked Bags\nInclude:\n□ Beach clothing\n□ Shoes\n□ Toiletries\n□ Sunscreen\n□ Chargers\n□ Souvenirs space\nHoneymoon Packing List\nParis\nBring:\n□ Comfortable walking shoes\n8\n\n□ Light jacket\n□ Umbrella\n□ Day bag\nAmalfi Coast\nBring:\n□ Swimsuits\n□ Cover-ups\n□ Sandals\n□ Sunglasses\n□ Sunscreen\n□ Beach tote\nCapri Boat Day\nBring:\n□ Swimsuit\n□ Waterproof pouch\n□ Sunscreen\n□ Sunglasses\n□ Hat\n□ Towel if desired\nPath of the Gods\nBring:\n9\n\n□ Sneakers\n□ Water bottle\n□ Hat\n□ Sunscreen\nDo NOT bring:\n□ Heavy backpack\n□ Excess gear\nPompeii\nBring:\n□ Sneakers\n□ Water\n□ Portable charger\n□ Hat\nPompeii offers very little shade.\nThe Golden Rule\nIf something is forgotten:\nDo not panic.\nParis has stores.\nItaly has stores.\nYou are not going into the wilderness.\nAlmost everything can be purchased if needed.\n10\n\nThe only truly irreplaceable items are:\n□ Passport\n□ Wallet\n□ Phone\n□ Medications\nEverything else is solvable.\nFinal Honeymoon Mindset\nThe objective is not to execute the itinerary perfectly.\nThe objective is to enjoy the honeymoon.\nIf a bus is missed:\nTake the next one.\nIf it rains:\nFind a café.\nIf you're tired:\nSleep in.\nIf you find somewhere beautiful:\nStay longer .\nThe memories will matter far more than the schedule.\nThe itinerary exists to support the honeymoon.\nThe honeymoon does not exist to serve the itinerary.\n11",
